Description: Lower body sherd of Attic, probably black-figured pottery open vessel, probably a krater; interior glazed black; exterior glazed save for lower left corner of a panel, which has thin vertical framing line; blob of glaze only preserved of decoration in panel; broad added red band below panel.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0842) (Phase 1)
